comments.body: @matthewjchandler @hectorcorrea Since there is no Product details page --  as of right now --  I have a "Product Details:" link_text pointing to the Tiger Data homepage. Is that ok for now or should I also setup a boilerplate page for it to link to? Is that necessary since that will be taken care of in issue [#264](https://github.com/pulibrary/tiger-data-app/issues/264) when the page actually gets created -- and we leave a note to comeback and update the link path?
@JaymeeH The project show page (https://github.com/pulibrary/tiger-data-app/blob/main/app/views/projects/show.html.erb) is the "Project Details"

@JaymeeH  My concern was mainly about the title that displays on the page for the user. It should be "Project Details: [insert project title]". I believe you all have been calling this the "show" page, where the project details are shown, but I've been calling it the "Project Details" page in my design materials
@hectorcorrea Oh ok, I misunderstood the original Issue description. So to clarify, this should not be actually linking to anything at all, correct? @matthewjchandler
@JaymeeH Yes, I don't have a need for a link out to a different page in this issue. It's really just about the page title displayed for the user
Since provenance and automatic settings are static (unchangeable) fields, should we be adding them to the edit form? @matthewjchandler
